summary: An Ordinance amending Section 2 of Ordinance No. 37183, entitled "An Ordinance authorizing and directing the Board of Public Works of the City of Seattle to lease to the Chief Seattle Film Company for a certain term of years, the south half of that portion of East Blaine Street lying between the east marginal line of Forty-second Avenue North and the west marginal line of Laurelshade Avenue, under certain terms and conditions", approved March 20, 1917.
